Since the CS/Sa-50 coating demonstrated the best anticorrosive properties among the coated samples, impedance results were obtained for this sample in Ringer solution for a long-term immersion (Fig. 8
                        ). From the Nyquist and Bode plots it is noticed that the capacitive diameter of the curves and the |Z| values increase with time at low frequencies up to 7 days and then decrease. The equivalent circuit shown in Fig. 9
                        c was employed to fit the data. From Tables 2 and it can be seen that the Rc value increases with time up to 7 days of immersion. Then the value drops at 10 days. Comparing the impedance values obtained for the CS/Sa-50 coating with those reported for other biopolymer-based coatings on Mg alloys, it can be concluded that the level of corrosion protection achieved is acceptable (Tian et al., 2023) (Beyzavi et al., 2023) (Vahedi et al., 2023) (Wang et al., 2022).
